subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Body elongate; body, head, and pronotum in general dark purple; elytra glabrous, shiny yellow, sides subparallel (
Fig. 10A
); clypeal emargination deep, narrow and rounded; clypeal lateral margin convex and produced, obtuse angle between outer side of anterior teeth and clypeal lateral projection (
Fig. 10C
); antenna with 10 antennomeres, yellow, club nearly twice as long as the funicle; posterior corners subangulate, obtuse; mesotibia cylindrical in cross section (
Fig. 10D
); pygidium slightly convex; wide, subtrapezoidal; pygidial disc glabrous or with unconspicous bristles throughout (
Fig. 10E
); males with inner margin of metatibia not carinate; transverse carina weakly defined; protarsomere II elongate; parameres narrowed at the midline; splitted after the midline; inner margins straight; apex spatulate (
Fig. 10F
).
